Alex J. Anderson began making ambient soundscapes and relaxation music for his mother on her journey with Cancer to aid with sleep and calm her anxiety.  Alex is grateful to be able to share the calming effects of music and sound with his community and hopes to reach people dealing with trauma, end of life patients, and people struggling to sleep or stay calm.  

His music is organic sounding as he uses vintage analogue synthesizers, real instruments, field recordings, and his own voice to create it.  Each song is a longform meditation, meant to be listened to in one sitting.  A journey in stages, meant to release the listener's conciousness, encourage a centered mind, and exit with purpose and solumness.

Alex also runs a record label that releases all types of music including ambient, electronica, techno, house, and more called Perpetual Joy.  Music is Joy, and our purpose is to spread that joy....read more
